[[File:PE-mapa-Brejão.png|thumb|right|250px|Brejão in [[Pernambuco]].]] '''Brejão''' is a municipality/city in the state of [[Pernambuco]] in [[Brazil]]. The population in 2009 was 9.780 and the total area is 159.79&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>.
==Geography==
* State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Agreste]] of Pernambuco * Boundaries - [[Garanhuns]] ('''N''' and '''E'''); [[Lagoa do Carro]] ('''S'''); [[Terezinha]] ('''W'''). * Area - 159.79&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> * Elevation - 788 m * Hidrography - [[Mundaú River]] * Vegetation - [[Subcaducifólia]] forest * Clima - [[Tropical]] hot and humid * Annual average temperature - 22.0 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 244&nbsp;km
==Economy==
The main economic activities in '''Brejão''' are related with [[agribusiness]], especially creations of [[cattle]]; and plantations of [[bean]]s, [[manioc]], [[coffee]] and [[tobacco]].
